      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/community/2017/03/24/time-address-devastating-impact-tb-indias-women</guid>
      <description>For women in India, being diagnosed with tuberculosis means a lifetime of persecution and rejection by community and family. But interventions to reduce stigma, like those that have worked for HIV, could provide a solution, say TB experts Amrita Daftary and Madhukar Pai.</description>
